com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface DateTime


  • public interface DateTime
    Represents the date and time (month, day, year, hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, and nanosecond) in a bandwidth-optimized fashion. This time value is represented as Greenwich Mean Time (GMT) unless noted otherwise

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Sets all members in DateTime to 0.

      • blank

        void blank()
        Sets DateTime to blank. Sets all members in DateTime to their respective blank values.

        • For date, all values are set to 0.
        • For time, hour, minute, and second are set to 255 millisecond is set to 65535, microsecond and nanosecond are set to 2047.

      • isBlank

        boolean isBlank()
        Returns true if all members in DateTime are set to the values used to signify blank. A blank DateTime contains hour, minute, and second values of 255, a millisecond value of 65535, microsecond and nanosecond values of 2047, and day, month and year value of 0.
        Returns:
        true if DateTime is blank, false otherwise.

      • isValid

        boolean isValid()
        Verifies the contents of a populated DateTime object. Determines whether day is valid for the specified month (e.g., a day greater than 31 is considered invalid for any month) as determined by the specified year (to calculate whether it is a leap year). Also validates the range of hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, and nanosecond members. If DateTime is blank or valid, true is returned; false otherwise.
        Returns:
        true if DateTime is blank or valid, false otherwise.

      • equals

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if dates and times are equal, false otherwise

      • toString

        java.lang.String toString()
        Convert DateTime to a String. Returns a String as "%d %b %Y hour:minute:second:milli:micro:nano" (e.g., 30 NOV 2010 15:24:54:627:529:436).
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        the string representation of this DateTime

      • value

        int value(java.lang.String value)
        Converts a String representation of a date and time to a DateTime. This method supports Date values following "%d %b %Y" format (e.g., 30 NOV 2010) or "%m/%d/%y" format (e.g., 11/30/2010). This method supports Time values that conform to "%H:%M" (e.g., 15:24) or "%H:%M:%S" (e.g., 15:24:54) formats as well as "hour:minute:second:milli:micro:nano" format (e.g., 15:24:54:627:529:436).
        Parameters:
        value - string containing an appropriately formatted string to convert from
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes.SUCCESS on success, CodecReturnCodes.INVALID_ARGUMENT if value is invalid.

      • value

        int value(long value)
        Sets date time from a number equal to milliseconds since the January 1, 1970 (midnight UTC/GMT) epoch. Must be a positive number.
        Parameters:
        value - number equal to milliseconds since epoch
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes.SUCCESS on success, CodecReturnCodes.INVALID_ARGUMENT if value is invalid.

      • encode

        int encode(EncodeIterator iter)
        Used to encode a date and time into a buffer.
        Parameters:
        iter - EncodeIterator with buffer to encode into. Iterator should also have appropriate version information set.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes.SUCCESS if success, CodecReturnCodes.FAILURE if failure, CodecReturnCodes.BUFFER_TOO_SMALL if the encode buffer is too small
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator, CodecReturnCodes
